The 2022 edition of the Zenith Bank tennis grand slam which started on Monday at the Tennis courts of the Ikoyi Club has entered crucial stages. Tournament’s favourite Destiny Da Silva had an easy ride over Amos Gagar with a straight sets of 6/2, 6/2 in one of the matches decided late on Tuesday just as Club Captain Ekene Nwaokolo defeated Victor Ufuoma 6/1, 6/3.In another encounter, Akinola Ayodeji was one set up with a 6-4 advantage before his opponent Labisi Abayomi scratched. Meanwhile, Layiwola Okoya, playing in the men singles B category defeated Celestine Ezeokoli 6/4, 6/1 just as Idris Bello-Osagie whipped Vishal Kirpalani 6/1, 6/1 The encounter between Segun Abijo and Sule Mustapha was one of the most explosive of the day. Abijo won the first set at 6/2 only for Mustapha to win the second 6/3. The decisive set kept the spectators at the edge of their seats but in the end it was Abijo who won the pulsating tie 10/6.   Falcons’ Nnadozie wins top French Women’s league award     Prudent Energy H’ball Premier League: Kano Pillars keep…     Over N60m jackpot for 8th Okpekpe Road Race   Other matches saw Peter Arikhan beating Chudi Igwe 6/2, 6/3 while Gaius Usoh defeated Charles Mozie 6/1, 6/2 just as Adedayo Ayoade also defeated Hilary Eledu 6/1, 6/2. In the Ladies singles, Taiwo Fanimokun walked over Bekeme Olowola while in the Men’s Veterans Singles category, Segun Durojaiye defeated Steve Ezeagu 3/6, 6/3, 10 – 4 in yet another tension soaked encounter as Durojaiye came back from a set down to beat Ezeagu. According to Nwaokolo, about 90 players will compete in the tournament which will be in six categories namely Men’s Singles A, Men’s Singles B, Ladies’ Singles, Veteran Singles (60+69) Super Veteran (70+) and Team tournament which would see a mixture of male and female players competing for honours under the various services platform of Zenith Bank. “We are having so much fun in the competition and the event is getting more and more competitive. As we approach the final stages, the true contenders are expected to emerge in various categories,” Nwaokolo said.